<p>

Mary-Jo Wormell along with two other prolific Mills &amp; Boon authors launched Heartline Publishing on 14th February 2001. The publishing house was meant to fill the gap between Mills &amp; Boon and Mainstream fiction. The publishing house appears to have closed as the website is now defunct. Wormell also was a Conservative Party parliamentary candidate.</p>

